= Visualize

Drawing and data visualization.

If you want to create more advanced drawings or plots, also have a look at the #link("https://github.com/johannes-wolf/cetz")[CetZ] package as well as more specialized #link("https://typst.app/universe/")[packages] for your use case.

== Definitions

- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/circle/")[circle]A circle with optional content.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/color/")[color]A color in a specific color space.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/curve/")[curve]A curve consisting of movements, lines, and Bézier segments.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/ellipse/")[ellipse]An ellipse with optional content.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/gradient/")[gradient]A color gradient.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/image/")[image]A raster or vector graphic.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/line/")[line]A line from one point to another.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/path/")[path]A path through a list of points, connected by Bézier curves.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/polygon/")[polygon]A closed polygon.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/rect/")[rect]A rectangle with optional content.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/square/")[square]A square with optional content.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/stroke/")[stroke]Defines how to draw a line.
- #link("/docs/reference/visualize/tiling/")[tiling]A repeating tiling fill.
